HEADWORD: Cassonade
<hw>Cas`son*ade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>casson</ets>, for <ets>caisson</ets> a large chest. This sugar
comes from Brazil in large chests.]</ety> <def>Raw sugar; sugar not
refined.</def> <rj><au>Mc Elrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

